Static - variables defined inside the class but outside any method, constructor, or block

Static is a keyword that can be used with variables, methods, and blocks

non static members cannot be used with static methods

STATIC
- static variables defined inside the class but outside any method, constructor, or block.
- cannot be local
- create a single copy of static variable and share among all instances of the class
- belongs to the class rather than the instance
- when you want to have common properties that should be passed onto all the instances that are static
- can be used with variables, methods, and blocks



4 types of access modifiers
private
default
protected 
public - making variables and methods accessible from anywhere throughout the entire project


syntax for variables
optional 				//optional  					//must    //must
 access modifier 		non-access mod static        dataType variableName;

Syntax for methods
optional 				//optional  					//must    //must
 access modifier 		non-access mod static          returnType  methodName